actions.text:
COMMANDS: Move around: N, E, S, W, UP, DOWN. 

Fill your belly: EAT OBJECT. 

Inventory/score: INV. 

Repeat location description: LOOK.
A BUOY rocks back and forth on the gentle waves, ringing as it sways. West leads back out to sea, further East is an island.
Sorry, that command doesn't do anything here
Waves lap against a sandy beach bathed in a red glow. West is the buoy. You notice something splashing around here - a naked WOMAN is on the surface!

You nibble playfully at her toes, then consume most of her main organs.

You are now @(percent(contact.fields.stomach_fullness / 100)) full!
The water tastes reassuringly bloody. You can follow the shore South.
You swim slowly through the night, contemplating the solitary brutality of your existence as an apex predator. Continuing South will bring you near some buildings after sunrise.

You are near a beach packed with holidaymakers. They look so happy. A black DOG is paddling with a stick in its mouth, and there's a young BOY on an inflatable. The south-west corner of the island is to the South.

It didn't suffer much, and no one seems to have noticed.

You are now @(percent(contact.fields.stomach_fullness / 100)) full!

You are near a beach packed with holidaymakers.

As you fulfill your primal urge, the holidaymakers notice and run screaming from the water.

You are now @(percent(contact.fields.stomach_fullness / 100)) full!

You are near a wooden pier with two MEN standing on it. You wonder if they are good friends. A chunk of MEAT is hanging on a chain in the water. West goes to the corner of the island, South leads out to sea, and East runs along the shore.
Sorry, that command doesn't do anything here
You are swimming alone out at sea as the sun sets. Between rumbles from your stomach you hear a bell ringing to the East.
Use HELP for a list of commands.

COMMANDS: Move around: N, E, S, W, UP, DOWN. 

Fill your belly: EAT OBJECT. 

Inventory/score: INV. 

Repeat location description: LOOK.
Sorry, that command doesn't do anything here
Sorry, that command doesn't do anything here
Sorry, that command doesn't do anything here
Sorry, that command doesn't do anything here
This ain't Leisure Suit Larry and you are a SHARK. What are you going to do, use a dorsal fin? Eat the woman dammit. EAT WOMAN.
Your teeth grind against metal as you wonder if the buoy feels loneliness.

COMMANDS: Move around: N, E, S, W, UP, DOWN. 

Fill your belly: EAT OBJECT. 

Inventory/score: INV. 

Repeat location description: LOOK.
You leap up and bare your teeth but can't reach them. They look at you with fear.

As you grab your snack, the chain pulls the pier apart. One man falls into the water but is rescued by his helpful friend. 

You are now @(percent(contact.fields.stomach_fullness / 100)) full.
You are near a broken wooden pier. Two MEN stand on the shore. West goes to the corner of the island, South leads out to sea, and East runs along the shore.
You leap up and bare your teeth but can't reach them. They look at you with fear.
You are off the south-west corner of the island. East takes you around to the southern shore, while West leads out to sea. The beach is North.
You are below a fishing VESSEL its nets symbolically blocking your way out to sea. The pier is to the North.
You tear into the hull, somehow managing to eat just one of the fisherman's eyes in the process.
You are now @(percent(contact.fields.stomach_fullness / 100)) full!
You are out at sea. The sun is warm on your dorsal fin and little fish bravely dart around you. Return to the coast East, or go DOWN to investigate a coral reef.
You are swimming just above a coral reef. A metal DRUM on the sea bed is covered in strange symbols and gives off a greenish glow. You can go back UP to the surface.

You don't feel any more full, but notice a warm, tingling sensation in your gut.
Added to inventory: @contact.fields.jaws_plutonium
You are swimming just above a coral reef. You can go back UP to the surface.

You are near the southern beach. There are boats, guns and people screaming, so you stay in deeper, more peaceful waters. East will take you into an estuary, the pier is to the West, or you can go South to leave this miserable island.
You are near the sea bed. A thick CABLE runs along it and strongly triggers your sense of electroperception. The surface is UP above.
As your teeth pierce the outer layers, hundreds of thousands of volts surge through your head before exploding your body.
You are in a small estuary which turns North into a pond or goes back out to sea to the West. You feel trapped and angry.
You are in the pond. There are YACHTS here with more people on them, happy people. You feel hungry and frustrated. The only exit is South.
You crash into the yachts, knocking people into the water. They are not so happy now.
You are in the pond. The police chief's SON is in the water, along with a MAN. When you attack one, the other may escape, so choose wisely. The only exit is South.

You take several bites and drag the man around. Meanwhile, the chief's son scrambles to safety.
You are now @(percent(contact.fields.stomach_fullness / 100)) full.

You snap it up immediately.

You are now @(percent(contact.fields.stomach_fullness / 100)) full.

You are in the pond. The only exit is South.
You are at sea, near an old BOAT with a noisy engine. There is BAIT on a line. The island is North.
You knock it about from below, loosening a few planks. You hear shouting, but the humans can not get you.

As you eat, a harpoon is fired into you with a barrel attached. You try to shake it off, and the boat is gone when you surface.

You are now @(percent(contact.fields.stomach_fullness / 100)) full.
You are south of the Island. It is peaceful here. You can swim DOWN deeper, or head South.
You are at sea. The island is North. The faint sound of jolly singing to the West awakens a fierce rage in you.
You have found the noisy old BOAT. On deck, the police CHIEF is throwing OFFAL in the water.

You grab small pieces at the surface and give the chief a scare. Two more harpoons are fired.

You are now @(percent(contact.fields.stomach_fullness / 100)) full.

Added to inventory: 2 Yellow barrels
You are below the BOAT. It has lowered a CAGE containing a DIVER who has come out to play.
You are on the boat. A shark HUNTER is slipping around on the deck amongst fishing and diving equipment. You can slide DOWN into the water.
You have severely damaged the boat. The stern is broken and sinking.

You almost get him, but he backs away and wedges a gas BOTTLE down your throat.

Added to inventory: Bottle
The bottle is jamming your mouth and making it hard to eat anything

As you leave the boat, the chief fires a rifle, hitting the explosive gas bottle with a lucky shot.
The plutonium in your stomach turns into an atomic fireball that triggers all-out nuclear war, destroying the world.

Your final score: @(percent(contact.fields.stomach_fullness / 100))
Use RESTART to play again.

You enjoy the morsel, but may have made a powerful enemy. Meanwhile the man scrambles to safety.

You are now @(percent(contact.fields.stomach_fullness / 100)) full.

You cannot reach him but give him quite a scare. Two more harpoons are fired.
Added to inventory: 2 Yellow barrels
You get no satisfaction from the slimy vegetation, but its removal reveals the diver.

The wetsuit is chewy, but you eventually get through it.

You are now @(percent(contact.fields.stomach_fullness / 100)) full.
You knock it about from below, loosening a few planks. You hear shouting, but the humans can not get you.

You give the despised shark hunter a gory death, and smash the cabin windows looking for more.

You are now @(percent(contact.fields.stomach_fullness / 100)) full.
With some effort you manage to expel the gas bottle, freeing up your jaws.

You feed one last time before swimming off into the sunset. Maybe tomorrow, you'll want to settle down. Until then you'll just keep moving on.

Your final score: @(percent(contact.fields.stomach_fullness / 100))

Use RESTART to play again.
You are below the BOAT and a broken CAGE. You can swim DOWN or leap UP on to the deck.
You are on a sea bed littered with pieces of non-biodegradable rubber. UP leads to the boat.

The man now safely standing on the shore says: "Life is one long pregame for death."
You sidle up next to the WOMAN and wink but can't seem to vocalize your thoughts. She looks impressed nonetheless and in a sultry rasp says: "Wanna get together and be bad for one another?"
Roses are red, violets are blue, love isn't real, everybody acts only in self interest.
Don't kiss me, I'm not a good idea right now.
You can't swim @run.results.response_1.category_localized here. Try typing LOOK to see where you are.

A meal missed, the nimble fish easily out manoeuvre your powerful jaws and disappear from view.
You sense a soggy peanut butter and jelly sandwich bobbing to the East, but don't recognise is as food.
